How to build All Purpose MD5 Jar

1.) Install Apache ant (http://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi) to a selected directory
2.) Ensure your JAVA_HOME environment variable contains the javac compiler.
3.) Ensure your ANT_HOME environment variable points to your ant installation.
4.) Run build.xml in the All Purpose MD5 Ant project (at command line, type: ant).

How to build IzPack installer
1.) ant generate-installer
2.) The installer cant be found in the All Purpose MD5 Ant directory



If you still run into problems with JAVA_HOME not being defined properly
follow the following instructions:

a. Go to Window > Preferences > Ant > Runtime
b. Choose the Classpath tab
c. Select the Global Properties node in the tree and click Add External JARs
d. Select tools.jar from your JDK directory (e.g., j2sdk1.4.2_03\lib\tools.jar)
e. Click Apply and OK

